<item>
            <title>[HTTPCORE-445] Path matching issue when a query string is present in the URI</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCORE-445</link>
                <project id="12310340" key="HTTPCORE">HttpComponents HttpCore</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If I register a handler with pattern &quot;/test*&quot; it successfully matches &quot;/test&quot; or &quot;/test/abcd&quot; but surprisingly it does not match &quot;/test?x=y&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;AsyncServerExchangeHandlerRegistry.create(HttpRequest)&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; 
78        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;final&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; i = path.indexOf(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;?&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
79        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (i != -1) {
80            path = path.substring(0, i - 1);
81        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Doing this removes the last character before the query string, &quot;/test?x=y&quot; becomes &quot;/tes&quot; which does not match.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I attached a sample class to reproduce the issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
